title: Grateful Dead Live at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium on 1973-06-09
lineage: transferred by Matt Smith, remastered by Monte Barry (some flaws remain) MAC tapes > Nak BX300 > Apogee Mini Me > Mini DAC (monitoring/mastering) > Lynx  One soundcard > Wavelab 5.0 > 24/96 FLACs > Samplitude Pro > TLH > CD Tag
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Deal, Looks Like Rain, They Love Each Other, Jack Straw, Loose Lucy, Mexicali Blues, Row Jimmy, El Paso, Box Of Rain, Sugaree, Beat It On Down The Line, Tennessee Jed, Greatest Story Ever Told, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Playin' In The Band, Loser, Me & My Uncle, Mississippi Half Step, Big River, Eyes Of The World-> China Doll, Sugar Magnolia

Sound check: China Cat->I Know You Rider. Do

reviews.review_text: - Sound-wise, maybe my favorite tape I've ever heard. Show-wise, I've heard them sound this sweet elsewhere, but never sweeter. Generally speaking, the first is the better of the two sets, but the second is still great, with a nice China Doll & finished off with a volcanic Sunshine Daydream.
Wow, awesome, vintage sound Thanks for taping / posting!  Excellent show, spine tingling at points.
